x4freetext: 3-MeV Argonne Van de Graaff Accelerator
Protons from accelerator incident on Li target
Small cylindrical samples (approximately 1 in. diameter
and 1-in. high) of metallic arsenic and sodium.
Time-of-flight.
A 7.2 cm**3 planar and a 30 cm**3 modified co-
axial Ge(Li) detector were used. Relative efficiency
curves for the detectors were measured using radio-
active sources of 133Ba, 22Na, 46Sc, 60Co and 154Eu
placed at the sample position.
Detector and shielding were rotated about sample
position permitting gamma ray angular distribution
measurements in the angular range 50-110 degrees
(lab).
Energies of the gamma rays were determined from a
quadratic polynomial calibration curve fitted to
calibration data acquired with the aid of radioactive
gamma ray sources. The counts in the full energy
peaks were determined by subtracting assumed linear
backgrounds from beneath the peaks.
Corrections were made for gamma attenuation in the
samples and for Ge(Li) detector efficiency. No
detailed corrections were made for neutron attenuation
and multiple scattering by the samples.
Correction due to the second group of neutrons in the
7Li(p,n) reaction was computed to be about 1.6% in
the worst case and negligible over most of the range.
